Terrible service. If you are not good at being a waitress don't be one. Had this short lady, such a careless person and was content with mediocrity. Don't do that, people go out to have a pleasant experience. My bar is not even that high. First don't have it go 15 min before you ask the person for their order. Once you get the order, get it right. If you don't get it right, apologize and see how you can fix the problem. Sometime throughout the service towards the middle hopefully go to the customer and ask if they want something or just check up on them. At least ask once. When you see the customer finished eating take the initiative to go over there and ask is there anything else you would like suggest a dessert maybe and if none than offer the check. Is that difficult? If being a waitress is not your first choice in life doesn't mean you shouldn't try to be good at it. You should try cause it's your job and the business you work for are depending on you to represent them properly. Stay at it do well at it until you find the job you finally want to do. Your character is being represented. I tried to be good at everything I got paid to do and sometimes things I didn't get paid for. If I couldn't be good at it I simply quit. I was told over the phone that the wait staff wouldn’t accommodate that request , because they’re very busy . I called right back and asked if I should therefore reserve a table . The person on the phone said it wasn’t really necessary , but said they’d hold one for us , and took my name . We ordered two burgers of course , I also got a Bloody Mary . I have been coming to Salty Dog for years.  Mike the bartender is awesome.  This is why I return with friends.  Also, I work in the neighborhood and always suggest to my coworkers to come here for happy hour.  However after a Friday night here, I will NEVER give Salty Dog my business ever again, and I hope none of you do as well.  Apparently sitting at table service is different than sitting at the bar.  You would think that spending almost $250 on drinks, they would offer some type of buy back.  Well they didn't.  So I asked the waiter to ask the manager.  He did and the "manager" said that he wasn't present during the whole time we were seated so he can't do anything.  They said that they can't buy back, but that Don Julio was supposed to be 14, and they only charged 11.  I thought that was ridiculous that this was the response I got.  I politely said that it wasn't possible after 6 hours of being here they can't take one drink off as a buy back.  I asked him to ask again.  He went, asked, and came back with "well we can do a buy back and give you a drink now."  I declined saying that we wanted to leave and just asked if they could knock off a drink.  I said that I wanted to speak to a manager or I'm not paying this bill until I speak to someone in charge.  He said that there was nobody there I could talk to except John and he told me that I didn't want to speak to him.  Why should I, as a customer, be scared to speak to a manager?  At this point, it's like where is the customer service?  Or why can't the customer just speak to management?  At least have the decency to come to the table, not dodge a customer's request to speak to management.  It's just courtesy.  Well here comes the bald man John like a big bad wolf SCREAMING at my face, "What?  What's your problem?  You don't want to pay your bill (meanwhile I have my credit card open in front of him) ?  Call the cops, have her arrested.  She doesn't want to pay the bill.  We don't want your business here anyway.  Call the cops."  I was mortified.  Not only did we spend $250, they added $47 gratuity on 3 people's tab.  and our bill came out to $304.  I had no problem paying the bill as the owner's daughter Nicole came and decided to take over and told me to deal with her.  Now embarrassing me in the middle of this place like I was a degenerate who couldn't pay a $ 300 tab, they swiped my card with no problem.  But Nicole had a comment or excuse for every thing I said.  I told her that I come here all the time, I'm good with the bartenders and take care of them since I'm one myself.  I always take care of Mike..she kept cutting me off and saying that Mike wasn't there tonight and table service was different.  I said it shouldn't even matter at that point.  How does that justify this man yelling at me at a reputable establishment in the community where children and families were around ok?  She proceeded to respond with, " Well the waiter did warn you about John." Then I pointed out how John and his posse in the corner were judging me like high school girls about my situation, not knowing the entire story.  I would've tipped the bartender $60 dollars because of our length of time there.  She said it's unfortunate that the waiter will suffer from this and I said yes, but management could've came to me and said unfortunately we can't comp, but the next one would be on the house.  Not offer the comp AFTER me having make a complaint.  Then on top of that have this man come at me humiliating and insulting me in the middle of the restaurant.  He was so disrespectful and needs to be taken out of this business.  It was outrageous and traumatic what I went through and I'm sure this man John thought he could speak to me that way because 1. He thought I was some dumb drunk.  2. I am an Asian woman who wouldn't stick up for herself.  Mind you, I wanted to fight back but I literally felt threatened and harmed that if I fought back he would've hit me because of how close he was at my face.  Completely and utterly disgusted.  WIll never give them my business again.  Period.

I was in BK visiting my best friend and ultimately met a younger cousin for a drink at old stomping grounds. I have SVT and if or when I have a drink, my doctor said to have a glass of water to prevent dehydration (mind you, I work as a medical professional). After a drink, I asked for a glass of water no problem. 2nd drink, the same. My younger cousin -sweetheart that he is, asked for a glass of water but the bartender AND OWNER said buy one. I decided to speak with the owner saying it was no problem getting a glass of water before because I have a heart condition, but because my male cousin asked for a glass of watee for me he was being charged and his reply was "SWEETHEART, I HAVE BILLS TO PAY. IF YOU HAVE A HEART CONDITION, DO ME A 'FAYVUGH' AND STAY HOME CUZ THE RENT DONT PAY ITSELF". That's nice SALTY DOG, 5 PATRONS left within a few minutes despite reviving your dying/dead bar and dropping over $200. If you had good memories there --- SAVE THEM because your better off doing the owner a favor and staying home. *Zero stars was not available* Lastly,  I have been a long time patron.  So this post comes from the bottom of my NY-er soul.
